<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
    <head>
        <meta charset="UTF-8">
        <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
        <link rel="stylesheet" href="./paste.css">
        <title>MTGPaste - Syntax</title>
        <style>
            #helptext{
                padding: 20px; 
                width: calc(100vw - 40px); 
                height: 100vh;
            }
            .code {
                color: rgb(176, 238, 176);
                background-color: #f1f1f11c;
                padding: 2px;
                display: inline-block;
                padding: 10px;
            }
        </style>
    </head>
    <body>
        <div id="helptext">
            <h1>MTGPaste Syntax</h1>
            <p1>A paste can contain any number of cards (allows up to 10,000 characters to be entered)<br>
                Set numbers and other information will be ignored.<br>
                Each card is represented by its first result on Gatherer that matches the name. <br>
                Card names can be lower case. "Cancel" will render the same as "cancel".<br>
                Each line must contain only one card with any of the formats outlined below.
            </p1>

            <h3>Xmage Format</h3>
            <div class="code">
                <p1>
                    1 [M15:44] Aetherspouts<br>
                    1 [H1R:10] Tribute Mage<br>
                    1 [5ED:408] Winter Orb
                <p1>
            </div>

            <h3>MTGO Format</h3>
            <div class="code">
                <p1>
                    1 Aetherspouts<br>
                    1 Tribute Mage<br>
                    1 Winter Orb
                </p1>
            </div>

            <h3>Arena Format</h3>
            <div class="code">
                <p1>
                    1 Aetherspouts (M15) 44<br>
                    1 Tribute Mage (H1R) 10<br>
                    1 Winter Orb (5ED) 408
                </p1>
            </div>
        </div>
        <script defer data-domain="mtg.skate.plib.dev" src="https://plausible.skate.plib.dev/js/script.js"></script>
    </body>
</html>